  "texts": [
    "Specifically, service members were nested within companies, and models included 8 contrast variables to account for battalion-level differences in the two study conditions.",
    "Participants were provided with the opportunity to select their platoon number using options provided (e.g., platoon 1, platoon 2) on the survey or through a typed response.",
    "However, some responses were unable to be stratified due to incomplete unit identification at upper echelons (e.g., missing company) or unsortable typed responses.",
    "Together, these issues would have diminished the sample size and posed concerns around statistical power.",
    "Therefore, the decision was made to use company identification as the cluster variable while controlling for battalion effects through the use of eight contrasts (four contrasts per condition)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}